(1735, 68, 'column_2', '<h3>Participants</h3>\r\n<strong>Michael Archer</strong>, Professor Biological, Earth &amp; Environment Sciences, University of New South Wales (Thylacine &amp; Lazarus Projects)\r\n\r\n<strong>Joel Berger</strong>, Senior Scientist, Wildlife Conservation Society &amp; Professor, University of Montana\r\n\r\n<strong>Hilary Bok</strong>, Associate Professor of Philosophy, Johns Hopkins University\r\n\r\n<strong>Stewart Brand</strong>, Revive and Restore, a project of The Long Now Foundation. Steering committee.\r\n\r\n<strong>David Burney</strong>, Professor of Conservation Paleobiology, National Tropical Botanical Garden\r\n\r\n<strong>Alejandro Camacho</strong>, Director, Center for Land, Environment &amp; Natural Resources, UC Irvine School of Law\r\n\r\n<strong>George Church</strong>, Director of the Center for Computational Genetics, Harvard Medical School. Steering committee.\r\n\r\n<strong>Alberto Fernández-Arias</strong>, Head of the Service of Hunting, Fishing and Aquatic Medium Wetlands, Aragon Government, Spain (Pyrenean ibex)\r\n\r\n<strong>John Francis</strong>, Vice President for Research, Conservation and Exploration, National Geographic Society\r\n\r\n<strong>Andrew French</strong>, A/Prof. at the Centre for Animal Biotechnology, University of Melbourne (Lazarus Project)\r\n\r\n<strong>Terry Garcia</strong>, Executive Vice President, National Geographic Society\r\n\r\n<strong>Tom Gilbert</strong>, Professor of Paleogenomics, University of Copenhagen (Ancient DNA)\r\n\r\n<strong>Hank Greely</strong>, Professor, Director of the Center for Law and the Biosciences, Stanford Law School. Steering committee.\r\n\r\n<strong>Michael Hofreiter</strong>, Professor for Evolutionary Biology and Ecology, The University of York (Ancient DNA)\r\n\r\n<strong>Insung Hwang</strong>, Researcher, Sooam Biotech Research Foundation (Woolly mammoth)\r\n\r\n<strong>Kate Jones</strong>, Professor of Ecology and Biodiversity, University College London and Zoological Society of London\r\n\r\n<strong>Peter Kareiva</strong>, Chief Scientist, The Nature Conservancy\r\n\r\n<strong>Henri Kerkdijk-Otten</strong>, Manager, Project TaurOs (Auroch)\r\n\r\n<strong>Robert Lanza</strong>, Chief Scientific Officer, Advanced Cell Technology (Gaur and Bucardo)\r\n\r\n<strong>Ross MacPhee</strong>, Curator &amp; Professor, American Museum of Natural History (Ancient DNA). Steering committee.\r\n\r\n<strong>Michael McGrew</strong>, Professor of Developmental Biology, The Roslin Institute, University of Edinburgh\r\n\r\n<strong>Ben J. Novak</strong>, BSc Ecology and Evolution, de-extinction researcher/science consultant, Revive and Restore\r\n\r\n<strong>Ryan Phelan</strong>, Revive and Restore, a project of The Long Now Foundation. Steering committee.\r\n\r\n<strong>Hendrik Poinar</strong>, Principle Investigator, Ancient DNA Centre, McMaster University (Woolly mammoth/Ancient DNA). Steering committee.\r\n\r\n<strong>William Powell</strong>, Director, Council on Biotechnology in Forestry, State University of New York (American Chestnut)\r\n\r\n<strong>Marilyn Renfree</strong>, Professor of Zoology, University of Melbourne (Tasmanian Tiger)\r\n\r\n<strong>Jean-Marie Rouillard</strong>, Co-founder and CSO, MYcroarray (genome synthesis)\r\n\r\n<strong>Oliver Ryder</strong>, Director of Genetics, San Diego Zoo Institute for Conservation and Research\r\n\r\n<strong>Mary Schweitzer</strong>, Professor of Marine, Earth and Atmospheric Sciences, North Carolina State University (Ancient DNA)\r\n\r\n<strong>Jacob Sherkow</strong>, Fellow, Center for Law and the Biosciences, Stanford Law School\r\n\r\n<strong>Jamie Shreeve</strong>, Senior Science Editor, National Geographic Magazine. Steering committee.\r\n\r\n<strong>Stanley Temple</strong>, Professor Emeritus, University of Wisconsin-Madison\r\n\r\n<strong>Frans Vera</strong>, Founder, Oostvaardersplassen and Director, Foundation Natural Processes\r\n\r\n<strong>Nathan Wolfe</strong>, Founder and CEO, Metabiota and Chairman, Global Viral\r\n\r\n<strong>Guojie Zhang</strong>, Associate Director of Scientific Development, BGI-Shenzhen\r\n\r\n<strong>Sergey Zimov</strong>, Director, Northeastern Science Station of Cherskii (Pleistocene Park)'),
