(16, 3, '2013-01-17 03:26:18', '2013-01-17 03:26:18', '<strong>1. Genomic revival questions</strong>\r\n\r\n<dl><dd>If we can revive an extinct species, should we?</dd><dd>Does it matter if the extinction was caused by humans?</dd><dd>Will de-extinction research help protect endangered species?</dd><dd>Are some species more desirable or ethical to bring back than others?</dd><dd>If the revival process involves interim stages of “chimaeric” (hybrid) creatures, is that a problem?</dd><dd>If a revived species is not quite genomically identical to the original, how close is close enough?</dd><dd>Is it ethical to “improve” a revived species—for example to make a formerly extinct bird resistant to avian malaria? (In Hawaii the disease has eliminated most endemic species of birds below 4,000 ft.)</dd><dd>What are the consequences of being able to revive a species and deciding not to?</dd><dd>Can revival techniques be patented?</dd><dd>Can revival techniques be kept secret?</dd><dd>Is it okay to revive a species strictly for commercial purposes?</dd><dd>As ethical standards emerge, what governance entities are responsible for oversight and enforcement?</dd><dd>De-extinction could become an amateur medium, the way breeding has. Is there a form of grassroots ethics that could make the practice self-governing?</dd></dl>&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2. Captive breeding questions</strong>\r\n\r\n<dl><dd>Is captive breeding of revived species any different from current captive breeding of endangered species?</dd><dd>How about creatures or plants that are part way to full revival, such as hybrid band-tailed/passenger pigeons?</dd></dl>&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>3. Return-to-the-wild questions</strong>\r\n\r\n<dl><dd>Do revived species have a “right” to be returned to the wild?</dd><dd>Should revived species be treated as invasive species if they are being returned to their former native habitat?</dd><dd>Should revived species be treated as genetically modified organisms?</dd><dd>Should Environmental Impact Reports be required before release?</dd><dd>What kind of ecological analysis should be required before release?</dd><dd>Is release to the wild irreversible?</dd></dl>', 'Ethics', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-4', '', '', '2013-01-17 03:26:18', '2013-01-17 03:26:18', '', 11, 'http://rare.sansink.com/11-revision-4/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
