\r\n            width: 830px;\r\n            height: 260px;\r\n            display: block;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n\r\n    </style>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h1 class="">Current Activities</h1>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class="tedx_wrapper">\r\n\r\n    <div class="span-12 append-1">\r\n\r\n\r\n        <h2 class="larger">Convening meetings and workshops of de-extinction pioneers</h2>\r\n\r\n        <ul class="bottom"><li>Convened an exploratory meeting at Harvard in February 2012 on reviving the passenger pigeon. (See report.)</li>\r\n        <li>Organized a private workshop for de-extinction pioneers October 23-24 at National Geographic. (See report.)</li>\r\n        <li>Planning a public conference for de-extinction pioneers and related specialists at National Geographic—TEDx DeExtinction, March 15, 2013. (See meetings.)</li></ul>\r\n\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class="span-7 last">\r\n        <img src="http://rare.longnow.org/Resources/tedxlive.jpeg" alt="" style="width: 270px;">\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class="span-12 append-1">\r\n\r\n    <h2>Commencing work on bringing back the passenger pigeon</h2>\r\n\r\n    <p>We arranged for grad student <a href="http://rare.longnow.org/projects.html">Ben Novak</a> to intern at George Church’s bioengineering lab at Harvard to refine his sequence data of ancient DNA from three <a href="http://rare.longnow.org/projects.html">passenger pigeon</a> specimens; to begin work on sequencing the band-tailed pigeon (the closest living relative of the passenger pigeon); and to sequence DNA from the mourning dove—a possible hybridizing species with the passenger pigeon. The work will provide necessary foundations for reviving the passenger pigeon and for ecological research important to restoring the species to its native habitat. In the spring of 2013 he joins Beth Shapiro’s ancient-DNA group at UC Santa Cruz.We arranged for grad student Ben Novak to intern at George Church’s bioengineer