(179, 1, '2013-01-17 21:05:53', '2013-01-17 21:05:53', '<style type="text/css">\r\n    .body_block {\r\n    font-size: 1.12em;\r\n    }\r\n    .body_block ul li {\r\n    margin-bottom: 4px;\r\n    }\r\n    .body_block h1 {\r\n    color: #94907e;\r\n    }\r\n    .body_block h2 {\r\n    font-size: 2em;\r\n    line-height: 1.2em;\r\n    font-family: "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Verdana, Arial, sans-serif;\r\n    }\r\n    .body_block ul {\r\n    margin-left: 30px;\r\n    }\r\n    .header_block form {\r\n    display: none;\r\n    }\r\n    .menu_block {\r\n    display: none;\r\n    }\r\n    .user_menu_block div {\r\n    display: none;\r\n    }\r\n    .roster_wrapper {\r\n    padding-top: 30px;\r\n    position: relative;\r\n    left: -80px;\r\n    margin: 25px 0 25px;\r\n    padding-left: 80px;\r\n    background: url(http://media.longnow.org/files/2/rare-roster-bg.jpeg) center center no-repeat;\r\n    width: 870px;\r\n    height: 280px;\r\n    display: block;\r\n    }\r\n    .roster_wrapper h2 {\r\n    color: #42413b;\r\n    }\r\n    .tedx_wrapper {\r\n    padding-top: 25px;\r\n    position: relative;\r\n    left: -40px;\r\n    margin: 20px 0 20px 0;\r\n    padding-left: 40px;\r\n    background: white;\r\n    width: 830px;\r\n    height: 260px;\r\n    display: block;\r\n    }\r\n</style>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h1 class="">Current Activities</h1>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class="tedx_wrapper">\r\n\r\n    <div class="span-12 append-1">\r\n\r\n\r\n        <h2 class="larger">Convening meetings and workshops of de-extinction pioneers</h2>\r\n\r\n        <ul class="bottom"><li>Convened an exploratory meeting at Harvard in February 2012 on reviving the passenger pigeon. (See report.)</li>\r\n        <li>Organized a private workshop for de-extinction pioneers October 23-24 at National Geographic. (See report.)</li>\r\n        <li>Planning a public conference for de-extinction pioneers and related specialists at National Geographic—TEDx DeExtinction, March 15, 2013. (See meetings.)</li></ul>\r\n\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class="span-7 last">\r\n        <img src="http://rare.longnow.org/Resources/tedxlive.jpeg" alt="" style="width: 270px;">\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class="span-12 append-1">\r\n\r\n    <h2>Commencing work on bringing back the passenger pigeon</h2>\r\n\r\n    <p>We arranged for grad student <a href="http://rare.longnow.org/projects.html">Ben Novak</a> to intern at George Church’s bioengineering lab at Harvard to refine his sequence data of ancient DNA from three <a href="http://rare.longnow.org/projects.html">passenger pigeon</a> specimens; to begin work on sequencing the band-tailed pigeon (the closest living relative of the passenger pigeon); and to sequence DNA from the mourning dove—a possible hybridizing species with the passenger pigeon. The work will provide necessary foundations for reviving the passenger pigeon and for ecological research important to restoring the species to its native habitat. In the spring of 2013 he joins Beth Shapiro’s ancient-DNA group at UC Santa Cruz.We arranged for grad student Ben Novak to intern at George Church’s bioengineering lab at Harvard to refine his sequence data of ancient DNA from three passenger pigeon specimens; to begin work on sequencing the band-tailed pigeon (the closest living relative of the passenger pigeon); and to sequence DNA from the mourning dove—a possible hybridizing species with the passenger pigeon. The work will provide necessary foundations for reviving the passenger pigeon and for ecological research important to restoring the species to its native habitat. In the spring of 2013 he joins Beth Shapiro’s ancient-DNA group at UC Santa Cruz.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="span-7 last">\r\n    <img src="http://rare.longnow.org/Resources/p1210136.jpeg" alt="" style="width: 270px;">\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class="dotted_break bottom-30 spacer-10"></div>\r\n\r\n<img src="http://media.longnow.org/files/2/rare-isac.jpeg" alt="" class="float_right"  style="width: 509px; margin-left: 15px;" />\r\n\r\n<h2>Helping develop norms and <a href="http://rare.longnow.org/ethics.html">ethics</a> for de-extinction practices.</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Stewart Brand and Ryan Phelan were interviewed by Walter Isaacson (author of Steve Jobs; CEO of Aspen Institute) about “Revive and Restore” at the Aspen Environment Forum in June. Video <a href="http://www.aspeninstitute.org/video/2012-aspen-environment-forum-bringing-back-dead-stewart-brand-ryan-phelan">here</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class="roster_wrapper">\r\n\r\n    <div class="span-13">\r\n        <div class="spacer-60"></div>\r\n        <h2>Developing a roster of potentiallly revivable species along with criteria that make them more or less practical and desirable to bring back to life. </h2>\r\n\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class="span-7 last right">\r\n        <img src="http://media.longnow.org/files/2/rare-roster.jpeg" alt="" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Encouraging an online “zoo” of the genomes of revivable extinct species along with the genomes of their closest living relatives. (An excellent genome zoo of living species is the Genome 10K project.)</h2>\r\n\r\n<img src="http://media.longnow.org/files/2/rare-genome10k.jpeg" alt="" class="bottom-10" />\r\n\r\n<p class="bottom">Ben Novak elaborates:</p> \r\n\r\n<blockquote style="font-size: 1.5em;" class="top-10">“We could create a database exactly like the National Center for Biotechnology Information''s GenBank, only specifically for extinct species, bringing together all the DNA work in one place on this subject. It would be a valuable tool for everyone working in ancient DNA. It could build off the list of "species to bring back". I''m thinking of a full list of extinct species within the age range that DNA is viable to retrieve, with some information on collections housing tissue or fossil material, taxonomy information, and some references to literature. In this way a person designing an ancient DNA project could find out what species have no previous DNA sequenced, what species do, and to what extent. With this list we can then append how suitable a species is for revival.” </blockquote>\r\n\r\n', 'Home Page', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '7-revision-12', '', '', '2013-01-17 21:05:53', '2013-01-17 21:05:53', '', 7, 'http://rare.sansink.com/7-revision-12/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(180, 1, '2013-01-17 21:15:34', '2013-01-17 21:15:34', '<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=1001>\r\n		<colgroup>\r\n			<col width=11>\r\n			<col width=226>\r\n			<col width=11>\r\n			<col width=12>\r\n			<col width=740>\r\n			<col width=1>\r\n		</colgroup>\r\n		<tr valign=top>\r\n			<td height=663 colspan=2>\r\n				<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=237>\r\n					<colgroup>\r\n						<col width=15>\r\n						<col width=207>\r\n						<col width=15>\r\n					</colgroup>\r\n					<tr valign=top>\r\n						<td width=15 height=15 style="background-image:url(Resources/item2f.png)"><img src="Resources/_clear.gif" border=0 width=1 height=1 alt="" style="float:left"></td>\r\n						<td width=207 height=15 style="background-image:url(Resources/item2fa.png)"><img src="Resources/_clear.gif" border=0 width=1 height=1 alt="" style="float:left"></td>\r\n						<td width=15 height=15 style="background-image:url(Resources/item2fb.png)"><img src="Resources/_clear.gif" border=0 width=1 height=1 alt="" style="float:left"></td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr valign=top>\r\n						<td width=15 height=633 style="background-image:url(Resources/item2fc.png)"><img src="Resources/_clear.gif" border=0 width=1 height=1 alt="" style="float:left"></td>\r\n						<td width=197 height=623 style="background-image:url(Resources/item2fd.png); padding:5px"><p class="style16"><strong><span class="style4"><strong><span class="style4">The first de-extinction project with direct involvement by Revive and Restore is the <span class="style98">passenger pigeon,</span> which was hunted  from a population of billions in the 19th century to zero in 1914.  There are some 1,500 preserved specimens with extractable DNA.</span></strong></span></strong></p>\r\n						<p class="style16"><strong><span class="style4"><strong><span class="style4">In February 2012 Revive and Restore organized a meeting at Harvard titled &#8220;<a href="ppworshop.html">Bringing Back the Passenger Pigeon</a>.&#8221;  It included bird experts such as Noel Snyder, Scott Edwards, David Blockstien, and Joel Greenberg, along with biotech experts George Church and Beth Shapiro.</span></strong></span></strong></p>\r\n						<p class="style16 f-lp"><strong><span class="style4"><strong><span class="style4">When word of that meeting got around, we were contacted by <span class="style98">Ben Novak</span>, a young expert in ancient DNA obsessed with reviving the passenger pigeon.  He was hired by Revive and Restore to work full time on the passenger pigeon project, starting with sequencing its nearest living relative, the band-tailed pigeon.</span></strong></span></strong></p>\r\n						</td>\r\n						<td width=15 height=633 style="background-image:url(Resources/item2fe.png)"><img src="Resources/_clear.gif" border=0 width=1 height=1 alt="" style="float:left"></td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr valign=top>\r\n						<td width=15 height=15 style="background-image:url(Resources/item2ff.png)"><img src="Resources/_clear.gif" border=0 width=1 height=1 alt="" style="float:left"></td>\r\n						<td width=207 height=15 style="background-image:url(Resources/item2fg.png)"><img src="Resources/_clear.gif" border=0 width=1 height=1 alt="" style="float:left"></td>\r\n						<td width=15 height=15 style="background-image:url(Resources/item2fh.png)"><img src="Resources/_clear.gif" border=0 width=1 height=1 alt="" style="float:left"></td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n				</table>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td height=663 colspan=2></td>\r\n			<td height=1070 rowspan=4><img src="Resources/p1210136.jpeg" border=0 width=740 height=1070 alt="P1210136" style="float:left"></td>\r\n			<td height=663></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr valign=top>\r\n			<td height=18 colspan=4></td>\r\n			<td height=18></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr valign=top>\r\n			<td height=362></td>\r\n			<td height=350 colspan=2 bgcolor="#ffffff" style="padding:6px"><p><span class="style5">Ben Novak studying Martha (on left), the last passenger pigeon in the world.  She died on September 1, 1914, at the Cincinnati Zoo.  She was preserved in ice and sent to the Smithsonian Institution in Washington DC, where she is occasionally displayed with a male (on right).  Note the red eye, iridescent neck feathers, red feet, and (in the male) peach-colored breast and blueish back.</span></p>\r\n			<p class="f-lp"><span class="style5">Ben Novak did grad work on ancient DNA at MacMaster University in Ontario, learned biotech skills at George Church&#8217;s lab in Boston, and will be working on passenger pigeon DNA and de-extinction in Beth Shapiro&#8217;s group at the University of California, Santa Cruz.</span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td height=362></td>\r\n			<td height=362></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr valign=top>\r\n			<td height=27 colspan=4></td>\r\n			<td height=27></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr class="f-sp">\r\n			<td><img src="Resources/_clear.gif" border=0 width=11 height=1 alt="" style="float:left"></td>\r\n			<td><img src="Resources/_clear.gif" border=0 width=226 height=1 alt="" style="float:left"></td>\r\n			<td><img src="Resources/_clear.gif" border=0 width=11 height=1 alt="" style="float:left"></td>\r\n			<td><img src="Resources/_clear.gif" border=0 width=12 height=1 alt="" style="float:left"></td>\r\n			<td><img src="Resources/_clear.gif" border=0 width=740 height=1 alt="" style="float:left"></td>\r\n			<td height=1><img src="Resources/_clear.gif" border=0 width=1 height=1 alt="" style="float:left"></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</table>', 'Species projects', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '33-revision-6', '', '', '2013-01-17 21:15:34', '2013-01-17 21:15:34', '', 33, 'http://rare.sansink.com/33-revision-6/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
